To compute the cost percentage:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Cost Percentage}&=\frac{\text{Costs}}{\text{Sales}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$415,000}{\$780,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.53}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The cost percentage is 0.53 or 53\%.**

To compute the Depreciation Rate:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Depreciation Rate}&=\frac{\text{Depreciation}}{\text{Beginning Fixed Assets}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$135,000}{\$1,350,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.10}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The Depreciation Rate is 0.10 or 10\%.**

To compute the Interest Rate:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Interest Rate}&=\frac{\text{Interest Paid}}{\text{Total Debt}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$68,000}{\$880,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.08}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The Interest Rate is 0.08 or 8\%.**

Now, let us compute the dividend payout ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Dividend Payout Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Dividend}}{\text{Net Income}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$30,000}{\$127,980}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.23}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The dividend payout ratio is 0.23 or 23\%.**

Now, let us compute the Capital Intensity Ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Capital Intensity Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Fixed Assets}}{\text{Sales}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,350,000}{\$780,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{1.73}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The capital intensity ratio is 1.73.**

Now, let us compute the Fixed Assets Ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Fixed Assets Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Fixed Assets}}{\text{Total Assets}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,350,000}{\$1,590,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.85}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The fixed assets ratio is 0.85.**

The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted sales growth of 20\%

Now, let us compute the increase in the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Sales}&=\text{Sales}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$780,000}\times{20\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$156,000}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the sales amounts to \$156,000.**

Now, let us compute the projected sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Sales}&=\text{Sales}+\text{Increase in Sales}\\[12pt]
&={\$780,000}+{\$156,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$936,000}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected sales is \$936,000.**

Now, let us compute the projected current assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Current Assets}&=\text{Total Assets}-\text{Fixed Assets}\\[12pt]
&={\$1,620,000}-{\$1,375,471.70}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$244,528.30}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected current assets is \$244,528.30.**

**The payout ratio as computed in step 14 is 23\%**
\
Now, let us compute the projected dividends:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Dividends}&=\text{Net Income}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$157,673.96}\times{23\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$44,240.73}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected dividends is \$44,240.73.**
&nbsp;

Now, let us compute the projected addition to retained earnings:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Retained Earnings}&=\text{Net Income}-\text{Dividends}\\[12pt]
&={\$157,673.96}-{\$44,240.73}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$113,433.23}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected retained earnings is \$113,433.23.**

Now, let us compute the taxes:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Taxes}&=\text{Taxable Income}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$238,899.94}\times{21\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$81,225.98}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected taxes is \$81,225.98.**

Now, let us compute the projected net income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Net Income}&=\text{Taxable Income}-\text{Taxes}\\[12pt]
&={\$238,899.94}-{\$81,225.98}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$157,673.96}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected net income is \$157,673.96.**

Now, let us prepare the pro forma balance sheet of the company:
&nbsp;
!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/3d9354c5-1340-499f-a5a9-2a890ea6332a-1641399082436451.png)

### Let's first provide the given income statement in the problem:

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Income Statement}
\end{array}
$$
$$
\begin{array}{lr}
\text{Sales}&\$780,000.00\\
\text{Cost}&415,000.00\\
\text{Depreciation}&135,000.00\\
\text{Interest}&\underline{68,000.00}\\
\text{Taxable Income}&\$162,000.00\\
\text{Taxes}&\underline{34,020.00}\\
\text{Net Income}&\underline{\underline{\$127,980.00}}\\
\\
\hspace{10pt}\text{Dividends}&\$30,000.00\\
\hspace{10pt}\text{Addition to RE}&\$97,980.00

\end{array}
$$


### Also, here is the given balance sheet: 

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Balance Sheet}
\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lrlr}
\text{Current Assets}&\$240,000&\text{Total Debt}&\$880,000\\
\text{Net Fixed Assets}&\underline{1,350,000}&\text{Owner's Equity}&\underline{710,000}\\
\textbf{Total Assets}&\underline{\underline{\$1,590,000}}&\textbf{Total Debt and Equity}&\underline{\underline{\$1,590,000}}

\end{array}
$$

### Compute the capital intensity ratio.

The capital intensity ratio is used to measure how much-fixed assets are used to generate revenue.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Capital Intensity Ratio}&= \dfrac{\text{Fixed Assets}}{\text{Sales}}\\[15pt]

&=\dfrac{\$1,350,000}{\$780,000}\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{1.73}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the capital intensity ratio is **1.73**.

### Compute the projected sales growth at 20%.

The projected sales growth is calculated by multiplying the current sales with the projected growth. 

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sales Growth}&= \text{Current Sales} \times \text{Growth Rate}\\[15pt]

&=\$780,000 \times 120\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$936,000}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected sales growth is **$936,000**.

### Compute the projected cost of sales.

The calculated cost of sales percentage of 53.21% will be used in calculating the project cost of sales.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cost of Sales}&= \text{Projected Sales} \times \text{COS Percentage}\\[15pt]

&=\$936,000 \times 53.21\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$498,045.60}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected cost of sales is **$498,045.60**.

### Compute the projected assets.

Assets are to be projected based on the projected growth. It is always assumed that assets will be adjusted in proportion to the projected growth,
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Assets}&= \text{Total Assets} \times \text{Projected Growth}\\[15pt]

&=\$1,590,000 \times 120\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$1,908,000.00}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected assets are **$1,908,000.00**.

### Compute the projected fixed assets using the fixed asset ratio.

The fixed asset ratio should be the basis for calculating the fixed assets.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Fixed Assets}&= \text{Total Assets} \times \text{Fixed Asset Ratio}\\[15pt]

&=\$1,908,000 \times 84.91\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$1,620,082.80}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the projected fixed assets are **$1,620,082.80**.

### Compute the depreciation expense.

Using the calculated depreciation rate of 10%, we will multiply it with the projected fixed assets.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Depreciation Exp}&= \text{Fixed Assets} \times \text{Depreciation Rate}\\[15pt]

&=\$1,620,082.80 \times 10\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$162,008.20}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the depreciation expense will be **$162,008.20**.

### Compute the tax expense.

The tax expense is calculated by multiplying taxable income with the tax rate.
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Tax Expense}&= \text{Taxable Income} \times \text{Tax Rate}\\[15pt]

&=\$207,946.20 \times 21\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$43,668.70}}

\end{aligned}
$$


Therefore, the tax expense is **$43,668.70**.

### Compute the dividends to be declared using the dividend payout ratio.


The payout ratio is 23.44%; this will be used in calculating the dividends to declare.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Dividends}&= \text{Net Income} \times \text{Payout Ratio}\\[15pt]

&=\$164,277.50 \times 23.44\%\\[15pt]



&= \boxed{\textbf{\$38,506.65}}

\end{aligned}
$$



Therefore, the projected dividend is **$38,506.65**.

### Compute the retained earnings.

The declared dividends are deducted from the net income, the remaining net income balance is the retained earnings, and this amount is added to the equity.

 $$
\begin{array}{lr}
\text{Net Income}&\$164,277.50\\
\text{Less: Projected Dividends}&\underline{38,506.65}\\
\textbf{Addition to Retained Earnings}&\underline{\underline{\$125,770.85}}

\end{array}
$$


Therefore, the addition to the retained earnings is **$125,770.85**.

### Compute the equity section of the balance sheet.

The equity section is calculated by adding the projected addition to the retained earnings and the current equity.

 $$
\begin{array}{lr}
\text{Equity}&\$710,000.00\\
\text{Add: Retained Earnings}&\underline{125,770.85}\\
\textbf{Projected Equity}&\underline{\underline{\$835,770.85}}

\end{array}
$$


Therefore, the projected equity is **$835,770.85**.

### Prepare Pro-forma balance sheet presenting EFN.


$$
\begin{array}{c}
\hspace{30pt}\textbf{Balance Sheet}
\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lrlr}
\text{Current Assets}&\$287,917.20&\text{Total Debt}&\$880,000.00\\
\text{Net Fixed Assets}&\underline{1,620,082.80}&\text{Owner's Equity}&\underline{835,770.85}\\
\textbf{Total Assets}&\underline{\underline{\$1,908,000.00}}&\textbf{Total Debt and Equity}&\underline{\underline{\$1,715,770.85}}\\[5pt]
&&\textbf{EFN}&\$192,229.15\\
&&\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\$1,908,000.00}}

\end{array}
$$
